                           Concise, well-written treatment of epochal theory of modern physics covers classical relativity and the relativity postulate,
                              time dilation, the twin paradox, momentum and energy, particles of zero mass, electric and magnetic fields and forces and
                              more. Only high school math needed. Replete with examples, ideal for self-study

